Text.Value: Hah! Knew I could smell sumfin' roasted. Thought it were just the dwarf.
Can this priestess heal people too, or does she just brand them?
I don't have a brand. Yet.
See for y'self. Head inside, and follow the sound o' squealin' novices.
Mark of the Absolute, innit? Shows our devotion to 'er.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He holds out his hand, showing the brand
EditorData.NodeContext: Too drunk to be overly bothered, but mildly annoyed

Text.Value: Show him your brand.
Show him your mark.
We'll show the damn rat that poisoned us. Mark my words. Ya don't mess with the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: Someone poisoned his mates. He's determined to find the killer.

Text.Value: You wanted to see my brand. Here, take a look.
Hold on. I was askin' you sumfin', wasn't I?

EditorData.NodeContext: Drunk, trying to remember what they were talking about.

Text.Value: Best see the priestess and get branded, mucker.

EditorData.NodeContext: He has been branded (by choice) and his arm is badly burned. He's too drunk to care too much though

Text.Value: You let her burn you? Why?
Priestess? Is she a healer, too?
Heh. Seen 'er carve more folk than she's cured. Still, she's a Chosen o' the Absolute now.
Just like I thought. Yers is prettier 'n mine. S'pose it does the job, though.
Shrug and leave.
It's good, innit?
Oh, yeah.
You wanted to see a brand that I don't have.
Heh. Seen 'er carve more folk than she's cured. Still, she's a Chosen o' the Absolute now.
Fink the Absolute wants me to 'ave another drink.
Makes it easier to decide who we kill and who we don't, too - so best get a move on, eh?
Well, go get one inside, then! But 'ave a drink first. It stings sumfin' proper.
Grab a drink afore you see the priestess, mucker. The brandin' stings sumfin' proper.

EditorData.NodeContext: He has been branded (by choice) and his arm is badly burned. He's too drunk to care too much though

Text.Value: Hey, can I see yer brand? The priestess gave me one, and I think she did it wrong.

EditorData.NodeContext: He has been branded (by choice) and his arm is badly burned. He's too drunk to care too much though

Text.Value: Leave.

Synopsis: A somewhat zealous goblin eager to tell us about the mark that the Absolute's followers have branded onto their flesh
